</div><div id='zzqqrglrd1k214lRiverRapidsGadget43' class='CRiverRapidsGadget-view-rapids CRiverRapidsGadget'> <h2>Rapid Summary</h2>
<table class='data_table'>
<tr class='row-0'>
<th>Mile</th>
<th>Rapid Name</th>
<th>Class</th>
<th>Features (<a href="/content/Wiki/view/id/river%3Ainfo%3Afeature_legend/">Legend</a>)</th>
</tr>
<tr class='row-1'><td class='big'>0.1</td><td class='big'><a href="#rapid1528">Z-Channel</a></td><td class=big>III</td><td><img alt="Hazard " src="/resources/images/rapid_icon/rapid_icon_hazard.gif"></td></tr>
<tr class='row-0'><td class='big'>0.2</td><td class='big'><a href="#rapid1529">Rubble Dam</a></td><td class=big>III</td><td><img alt="Hazard " src="/resources/images/rapid_icon/rapid_icon_hazard.gif"></td></tr>
<tr class='row-1'><td class='big'>0.5</td><td class='big'><a href="#rapid1530">Midway Surfing</a></td><td class=big>III</td><td><img alt="Playspot " src="/resources/images/rapid_icon/rapid_icon_playspot.gif"></td></tr>
<tr class='row-0'><td class='big'>1.5</td><td class='big'><a href="#rapid1531">Little Falls</a></td><td class=big>III+</td><td><img alt="Hazard " src="/resources/images/rapid_icon/rapid_icon_hazard.gif"><img alt="Playspot " src="/resources/images/rapid_icon/rapid_icon_playspot.gif"></td></tr>
</table>
<h2>Rapid Descriptions</h2>
<div><div id='zzqqrglrd1k214lRiverRapidView44' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid1528">Z-Channel</a></b> (Class III, Mile 0.1)<br>
Z-Channel starts off as an easy eddy-hop. But the final drop is Class III with a pinning rock right in the middle. Watch for strainers here.<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqqrglrd1k214lRiverRapidView45' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid1529">Rubble Dam</a></b> (Class III, Mile 0.2)<br>
Run the rubble dam center left through a twisty, rocky channel. <br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqqrglrd1k214lRiverRapidView46' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid1530">Midway Surfing</a></b> (Class III, Mile 0.5)<br>
Great surfwaves in the upper portion of the run are easiest to catch as the river level drops. 2.7-2.9 ft. are premium. <br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqqrglrd1k214lRiverRapidView47' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid1531">Little Falls</a></b> (Class III+, Mile 1.5)<br>
Little Falls is the main attraction for this run. The left line (Maryland) is easy II-III at most levels. The right line (Virginia) is III+ to -IV, depending on the river and tide levels. <br>
<br clear=right>
</div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
